data.comment: The big names in today's match at Östgötaporten have now been confirmed.
The match is underway in Norrkoping.
In the minute 1, Can Norrkoping get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in AIK's half?
AIK are too eager and fall into an offside trap.
AIK drives forward and Paulos Abraham gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
In the minute 3, AIK have been awarded a corner by Kristoffer Karlsson.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to Norrkoping in their own half.
In Norrkoping Norrkoping drive forward through Christoffer Nyman. His shot is on target but it's saved.
In the minute 5, Sead Haksabanovic for Norrkoping drives towards goal at Östgötaporten. But the finish is unsuccessful.
Ball safe as AIK is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to Norrkoping.
In the minute 7, It's a goal kick for the away team in Norrkoping.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
In Norrkoping a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In the minute 9, Norrkoping's Lars Gerson is on target but unsuccessful.
AIK have a goal kick.
AIK awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In the minute 12, Free kick for Norrkoping in their own half.
Can Norrkoping capitalize from this throw-in deep inside AIK's half?
Corner awarded to Norrkoping.
In the minute 15, Henrik Castegren (Norrkoping) powers in a header – against the bar!
It's getting dangerous! Free kick for Norrkoping close to the penalty box.
Norrkoping push forward at Östgötaporten and Sead Haksabanovic gets in a great header. The attempt is cleared by the AIK defence.
In the minute 16, Norrkoping to take a throw-in in AIK territory.
Kristoffer Karlsson awards the away team a throw-in.
Throw-in AIK.
In the minute 18, Kristoffer Karlsson signals a Norrkoping throw-in in AIK's half.
Throw-in for Norrkoping in the half of AIK.
Norrkoping pushes forward through Isak Bergmann Johanneson, whose finish on goal is saved.
In the minute 21, AIK awarded a free kick in their own half.
Throw-in for Norrkoping at Östgötaporten.
Norrkoping's Jonathan Levi gets in a shot on goal at Östgötaporten. But the effort is unsuccessful.
In the minute 23, Throw-in for AIK in their own half.
Free kick for AIK in the half of Norrkoping.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a AIK throw-in in Norrkoping's half.
In the minute 26, Corner awarded to AIK.
Goal! AIK take a 0-1 lead through a well-placed header from Henok Goitom.
Great play from Sebastian Larsson to set up the goal.
In the minute 27, Kristoffer Karlsson awards the away team a throw-in.
Can Norrkoping get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in AIK's half?
Sebastian Larsson of AIK gets in a strike, but is off target.
In the minute 28, Kristoffer Karlsson awards Norrkoping a goal kick.
Goal kick for Norrkoping at Östgötaporten.
Norrkoping awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In the minute 34, A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
Norrkoping to take a throw-in in AIK territory.
Kristoffer Karlsson waits before resuming play because Christoffer Nyman for Norrkoping is still down.
In the minute 37, Jens Gustafsson (Norrkoping) is making a first substitution, with Simon Thern replacing Christoffer Nyman.
Norrkoping have a dangerous throw-in.
Throw-in high up the field for Norrkoping in Norrkoping.
In the minute 41, Simon Thern of Norrkoping smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
Free kick for AIK in their own half.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to AIK in their own half.
In the minute 45, Norrkoping awarded a free kick in their own half.
Kristoffer Karlsson will wait an extra 1 minutes before blowing the whistle to end the 1st half.
Norrkoping have been awarded a corner by Kristoffer Karlsson.
In the minute 45, The ref's whistle signals the end of the first-half.
The second-half has started.
Jonathan Levi gets an equalizer for Norrkoping. The score is now 1-1.
In the minute 46, That's a fine assist from Sead Haksabanovic.
Ball safe as AIK is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Throw-in for AIK in their own half.
In the minute 49, Throw-in for Norrkoping close to the penalty box.
Norrkoping's Jonathan Levi is on target but unsuccessful.
Sead Haksabanovic (Norrkoping) gets in a strike but the shot is blocked by a defender.
In the minute 50, Corner awarded to Norrkoping.
Norrkoping move into a 2-1 lead through a Henrik Castegren header.
Sead Haksabanovic with an assist there.
In the minute 51, Free kick Norrkoping.
In Norrkoping a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Norrkoping drive upfield and Filip Dagerstal gets in a shot. The strike is blocked by a AIK defender.
In the minute 54, Norrkoping have been awarded a corner by Kristoffer Karlsson.
In Norrkoping, Filip Dagerstal (Norrkoping) misses the target with a header.
Ball goes out of play for a AIK goal kick.
In the minute 55, In Norrkoping, Eric Kahl of AIK is presented with a shooting opportunity. But the strike is blocked by the covering defence.
AIK have been awarded a corner by Kristoffer Karlsson.
AIK's Eric Kahl gets in a shot but it is blocked by a Norrkoping defender.
In the minute 56, Important block from the AIK defence as Jonathan Levi fires in a strike for Norrkoping.
So close for Norrkoping as Jonathan Levi's shot comes back off the post.
AIK awarded a free kick in their own half.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to AIK in their own half.
In the minute 61, The away team have replaced Robert Lundstrom with Mikael Lustig. This is the first substitution made today by Bartosz Grzelak.
AIK make their second substitution with Kolbeinn Sigthorsson replacing Filip Rogic.
In the minute 61, Lars Gerson (Norrkoping) has received a yellow card from Kristoffer Karlsson.
AIK needs to be cautious. Norrkoping have an attacking throw-in.
Throw-in Norrkoping.
In the minute 66, Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to Norrkoping.
Erick Otieno is on a sub for Erik Ring for AIK.
The away team replace Enock Kofi Adu with Bilal Hussein.
In the minute 69, Throw-in for AIK at Östgötaporten.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a throw-in for Norrkoping, close to AIK's area.
Goal kick for AIK at Östgötaporten.
In the minute 71, Kristoffer Karlsson awards the home team a throw-in.
Free kick for Norrkoping in the half of AIK.
Sebastian Larsson (AIK) gets booked by Kristoffer Karlsson, and will miss the next match due to the number of yellow cards received this season.
In the minute 73, Kristoffer Karlsson awards AIK a goal kick.
Ball goes out of play for a Norrkoping goal kick.
Free kick Norrkoping.
In the minute 75, Per Karlsson is booked for the away team and will be suspended from the next match.
Corner awarded to AIK.
AIK have been awarded a corner by Kristoffer Karlsson.
In the minute 79, Throw-in for Norrkoping in the half of AIK.
Throw-in AIK.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a free kick to Norrkoping.
In the minute 80, Stefan Silva is replacing Paulos Abraham for AIK at Östgötaporten.
Throw-in for AIK in their own half.
Kolbeinn Sigthorsson gets his shot on target but fails to score for AIK.
In the minute 83, Norrkoping have a goal kick.
Egzon Binaku is replacing Sead Haksabanovic for the home team.
Filip Dagerstal is down and play has been interrupted for a few moments.
In the minute 85, Norrkoping’s Filip Dagerstal is on his feet again at Östgötaporten.
Corner awarded to AIK.
Henok Goitom (AIK) goes for goal but the shot is blocked by an alert defence.
In the minute 86, Corner awarded to AIK.
Penalty! Kristoffer Karlsson points to the spot, great chance for AIK...
Goal! Sebastian Larsson makes it 2-2. The equalizer came in the form of a penalty.
In the minute 88, AIK to take a throw-in in Norrkoping territory.
AIK are in shooting range from this free kick.
Sebastian Larsson gets his shot on target but fails to score for AIK.
Can Norrkoping capitalize from this dangerous free kick?
At Östgötaporten the fourth official shows that 5 minutes will be added to the 2nd half.
In Norrkoping a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Norrkoping drives forward and Isak Bergmann Johanneson gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Norrkoping.
AIK awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Kristoffer Karlsson signals a Norrkoping throw-in in AIK's half.
Kristoffer Karlsson blows to end the match. The final score is 2-2.
Kevin Alvarez is replacing Jonathan Levi for the home team.
Eric Kahl for AIK has been booked by Kristoffer Karlsson and receives a first yellow card.
